sentences: Donzella Petty-John, known professionally as Nella Dodds (born January 25, 1950) is an American soul singer and actress.
Born in Havre de Grace, Maryland, United States, she recorded six released singles for Wand Records between 1964 and 1966.
"Come See About Me" / "You Don't Love Me Anymore" - 1964 (Wand 167)
Reached number 74 in Billboard chart, November 28, 1964
"Finders Keepers, Losers Weepers" / "A Girl's Life" - 1964 (Wand 171) Reached number 96 in Billboard chart, January 16, 1965
"Finders Keepers, Losers Weepers" / "A Girl's Life" - 1964 (Wand 171) Reached number 96 in Billboard chart, January 16, 1965
Although Dodds was scheduled to have a vinyl album released in the mid 1960s, it was never released.
